    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/130">Heinricus</persName> servus servorum Christi et
                        Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus secundum
                        voluntatem dei salvatoris nostrique liberatoris. Quicquid confirmacionis et
                        proprietatis ad eclesiarum dei sanctorumque suorum exaltatione prebuerimus,
                        id nobis ad aeterne beatitudinis bravium et secularis vite profectum esse
                        profuturum verissime credimus. Igitur omnium sancte dei ecclesie fidelium
                        nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac futurorum agnoscat universitas, qualiter
                        nos pro dei omnipotentis amore et pro anima amite nostre <persName
                            key="#Offersio/donatio #Queen" ref="#people/1301">Adheleidis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Queen">imperatricis</rs> auguste et ob remedium anime nostrae
                        parentumque nostrorum, rogante domno <persName key="#Abbots"><name
                                ref="Andreas">Andrea</name></persName> venerabili <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbate</rs>, suo <rs key="#Monasteries">coenobio</rs> ad honore
                            <orgName
                            key="#Rivers #Mountains #Villas #Curtes #Mansi #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Saltworks #Mills #Penalty #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Castle #Ports #Other_administrative_unit #Assembly #Angaria #Tolls #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Immunity #Churches #Monasteries #Abbots #Monks #Royal_slave #Royal_aldius"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3619">sancti Salvatoris</orgName> haud procul a
                        menibus <placeName ref="#places/65">Ticinensis</placeName> urbis fundato per
                        hoc nostrum imperiale preceptum, prout iuste et legaliter valemus,
                        confirmamus, quemadmodum ad antecessores meos praeceptali auctoritate
                        confirmata sunt, omnia, que eiusdem venerabili loco donata collata et oblata
                        sunt tam de <rs key="#Offersio/donatio">largifluo dono</rs> memorate amite
                        nostre quam etiam aliqua inscriptione cartarum aliorum hominum, cum <rs
                            key="#Castle">castellis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Curtes">cortibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_slave">ancillis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_aldius">aldianibus</rs> et <rs key="#Royal_aldius"
                            >aldianis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">capellis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">oratoriis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Villas">villis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mansi">mansis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Landed_possessions">campis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mountains">montibus</rs> vallibus planiciebus <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Fisheries">piscacionibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs> terris cultis et incultis <rs
                            key="#Tolls #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Ports">portibus</rs>, verum etiam cum omnibus, de quibus
                        venerabili coenobium iuste investituram habet vel habuit ex ea die, qua
                        prefata serenissima amita nostra <rs key="#Monks">monachos</rs> ibi
                        constituit. Confirmamus quidem et firmissimam traditione largimur eidem
                        monaster[i]o domini Salvatoris <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property
                                #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            >sancti Anastasii</orgName> una cum <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Curtes 
                            #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/342">
                            <geogName
                                key="#Curtes 
                                #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#estates/134">Olonna</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Montecelli</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Erbaria</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >B[asilig]utiam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Frisinariam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Pastorianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Riuoceruinum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Tullianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Puizolum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Centascum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Noue</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Urba</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/18">Marinco</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Corianum</placeName> cum omnibus pertinentiis suis, <rs key="#Castle"
                            >castellum</rs> da <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Bosco</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Felegariolo</placeName>, terram de <persName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><name ref="Petrus Albesanus"> Petro Albesano</name></persName>,
                        terram quam tenuit <persName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><name ref="Liudualdus">Liutaldus</name></persName> cum <rs
                            key="#Mansi">manso</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <geogName key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Pelenzona</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Armentaria</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Blundi</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Gagio</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Lagusianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Cassina</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Cuguzuda</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Garlascum</placeName> cum <rs key="#Other_administrative_unit"
                            >districtum</rs> in circuitu duo miliarium una cum <rs key="#Forests"
                            >silva</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Carbonaria</placeName>, de quantum ian dictum monasterium per
                        praeceptum tenere videtur, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Uirgemini</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Caucon[a]te</placeName>, <rs>viridiarium</rs> prope Palatinam portam et
                        sancti Iohannis scitum cum omnibus pertinentiis et adiacentiis suis tam
                        infra civitatem Ticinensem quam extra, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Garfiniana</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Uicolongo</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Bissione</placeName>, <rs key="#Churches">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >sancti Nazarii</orgName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Mauratica</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Melaria</placeName>. Insuper monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sancte dei genitricis Marie</orgName> in
                        loco <placeName ref="#places/4179">Pomposa</placeName> constructum, cum
                        quibus ad eum pernere videtur, vel etiam omnes <rs key="#Saltworks"
                            >salinas</rs>, qua in <placeName key="#Saltworks" ref="#places/485">
                            Comaclo</placeName> ab supra scripto monasterio domini Salvatoris
                        pertinere decernitur seu in aliis omnibus locis, que ian dicto coenobio
                        sancti Salvatoris pertinere cernuntur, illo in proprium corroboramus.
                        Precipientes itaque iubemus, ut nullus episcopus dux marchio comes vicecomes
                        castaldius <rs key="#Immunity">nullaque imperii nostri magna parvaque
                            persona de rebus mobilibus sive immobilibus sive de qualibet terra
                            disvestere [i]dem monasterium sine legali iudicio presumat</rs>.
                        Sancimus insuper et hac nostra imperiali aucto[ri]tate concedimus, ut, si
                        contigerit, quod sepe accidit, quatinus abbas prenominati monasterii huius
                        lucis habitaculum deserat, liceat <rs key="#Monks">monachos</rs> ex sinu
                        eiusdem ecclesie q[uem meli]orem viderint eligere in <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >patrem</rs>, omnium episcoporum vel omnium mor[talium contradi]ccione
                        remota, nec fas sit alicui monacho ex alio monasterio ad id transitum facere
                        sine voluntate monachorum inibi deo servientium in perpetuum. Si quis autem
                        huius nostrae promulgate auctoritatis et preceptis violator extiterit sive
                        praedicte ecclesie sancti Salvatoris minorationem facere aut in castellis
                        villis vel aliquibuslibet locis eius aribergare, <rs key="#Assembly"
                            >placitum</rs> sine eiusdem coenobii abbatis iussione ullatenus tenere
                        aut aliquam <rs key="#Angaria">angariam</rs> vel publicam functionem aut <rs
                            key="#Teloneum">theloneum</rs> extorquere vel tollere aut monachos de
                        aliqua re presumpserit molestare, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty"
                            >auri cocti libras mille</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere
                            nostre</rs> ac medietatem <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">
                            abbati</rs> eiusdem monasterii qui pro tempore fuerit, et insuper, quod
                        ei deterius est, cum Iuda traditore domini salvatoris nostri, in cuius
                        nomine ian dictum monasterium constructum est, aeternis deputetur incendiis.
                        Ut autem verius credatur hoc preceptum nostra auctoritate peractum,
                        presentem paginam manu propria, ut videtur infra, corroborante sigillo
                        nostro iussimus insigniri. Signum domni Heinrici (M.) invictissimi
                        imperatoris augusti. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Heinricus"
                                >Heinricus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> vice <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"><name ref="Everardus"
                            >Euerardi</name></persName> episcopi et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovit. (SI. D.) </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
